			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;[Please summarize the enhancement so it will be comprehensible to someone&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;from outside the Native Client team. A good summary will include:]&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Most code refers to &amp;quot;all&amp;quot; of the structure needed by the x86-32 validator, even when it is only accessing small subcomponents of the validator.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
This makes unit testing harder, since one needs to &amp;quot;reconstruct&amp;quot; a full validator data structure for every unit test.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Componentize the data structures better so that (except for occational pointers), only data needed to call functions within a module need to be modeled.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Done when able to write unit tests without needing to model lots of extra data structures.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;[for users as well as other parts of the system]&lt;/b&gt;
